<h3>Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2013: Mobile Security</h3>
	  <p>On March 8, the Computer Science Department hosts the Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2013. Join us as we consider mobile security from a variety of perspectives presented by speakers who are forerunners in their fields. </p>
	  <p>More information about the conference and registration can be found at the <a href="conferences/cddr2013.html">conference website</a>. </p>
	  <hr />
	  <h3>Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2013: Mobile Security</h3>
	  <p>On March 8, the Computer Science Department hosts the Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2013. Join us as we consider mobile security from a variety of perspectives presented by speakers who are forerunners in their fields. </p>
	  <p>More information about the conference and registration can be found at the <a href="conferences/cddr2013.html">conference website</a>. </p>
	  <hr />
	  
<h3>Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2012: IT Evolution's Societal Impact</h3>
	  <p>On March 9, the Computer Science Department hosts the Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2012.  Come join us as we look at our increasing dependence on well-behaved computers both today and looking to the future. We will consider when and how we should question the risks from IT being involved in everything from our basic privacy to life-critical systems. As in past years, we also endeavor to offer other topics at the conference to diversify and enrich your experience. </p>
	  <p>More information about the conference and registration can be found at the <a href="conferences/cddr2012.html">conference website</a>. </p>
	  <hr />

   <h3>Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2011: Securing the Human </h3>
	  <p>On March 11, the Computer Science Department hosts the Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2010. This is one-day conference featuring distinguished guest speakers and SANS Training. Our goal is with this conference is to offer  information to allow you and your organization to secure employees,  contractors, IT staff, and management against these risks. </p>
	  <p>More information about the conference and registration can be found at the <a href="conferences/cddr2011.html">conference website</a>. </p>
	  <hr />
	  <h3>Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2010: Protecting Yourself and Your Business from International Threats </h3>
	  <p>On March 12, the Computer Science Department hosts the Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2010. This is one-day conference featuring distinguished guest speakers and SANS Training. </p><p>More information about the conference and registration can be found at the <a href="conferences/cddr2010.html">conference website</a>. </p>
      <hr />
      <p>On March 13, the Computer Science Department hosts the Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2009. This is a one-day program   addressing the critical issue of ptotecting data. More information about the conference and registration can be found at the <a href="conferences/cddr2009.html">conference website</a>. </p>
      <hr />
      <h3><strong>workshop on   computer security </strong> </h3>
      <p>On September 9, 2008, the Computer Science Department held a workshop on   computer security called Computer Security is Good Business. The workshop is cosponsored by NIST, the Small Business   Administration, and the FBI&rsquo;s InfraGard program. Materials about the workshop: <a href="conferences/workshop2008/outreach.pdf">Small &amp; Medium-Sized Business   Outreach</a>, <a href="conferences/workshop2008/flyer.doc">Flyer</a>, <a href="conferences/workshop2008/agenda.pdf">Workshop Agenda</a>.</p>
      <hr />
      <h3><strong>Cyber   Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference: Protecting our Infrastructure   Assets</strong> </h3>
      <p>The Computer Science Department  hosted the Cyber   Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference: Protecting our Infrastructure   Assets. This is a one-day interactive   conference addressing the critical issue of protecting our infrastructure   assets. Breakout sessions  considered this issue from different perspectives.   The conference futured several distinguished guest speakers: <a href="conferences/cddr2008/Finn.pdf">Bruce Finn</a>, <a href="conferences/cddr2008/Thompson.pdf">Jeff Thompson</a>, <a href="conferences/cddr2008/Miller.pdf">Steven Miller</a>, <a href="conferences/cddr2008/Edgar-Nevill.pdf">Denis Edgar-Nevill</a>, <a href="conferences/cddr2008/FBITeam.pdf">the FBI Response Team</a>, and <a href="conferences/cddr2008/Cheviron.pdf">Mark Cheviron</a>. The conference   was held on March 7th, 2008. The brochure of the conference can be found <a href="conferences/cddr2008/CyberConferenceBrochure2008rev.pdf">here</a>.</p>
      <hr />
      <h3>Cyber  Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference: Planning for Pandemic Crisis</h3>
      <p>On March 9, 2007, the Computer Sceince Department hosted the Cyber  Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference: Planning for Pandemic Crisis. The  Conference 
        addressed the impact of high absenteeism in the event of a cross sector
        pandemic crisis. What happens when a large number of employees don&rsquo;t
        show up for work due to illness, caring for family members or quarantine?
        How can industry leaders plan for cyber attacks that might occur
        when the workplace is vulnerable? How will national infrastructures protect
      digital assets with a 60% projected absentee rate? Invited speakers were Leonard Bailey 
Senior Counsel, Computer Crime Section Information Infrastructure Protection; Scott McPherson Chief Information Officer,
Florida House of Representatives; Kyle Belz, Director, Corporate Health and Safety American Red Cross. The brochure of the conference can be found <a href="conferences/cddr2007/brochure.pdf">here</a>.</p>
      <hr />
      <h3>The Cyber Defense and Disaster Recovery Conference 2006</h3>
      <p>The Computer Science Department organized and hosted  a one-day conference addressing        the critical issue of emergency response and disaster recovery. Keynote speakers will gave
        presentations of current issues. Attendees learned effective techniques and participate in a
        tabletop exercise based on a realistic disaster scenario. Keynote speakers were Dr. Newton Howard,
        Center for Advanced Defense Studies,
        Washington, D.C.; Dr. Roy Campbell
        Sohaib and Sara Abbasi Professor in
        Computer Science, UICU; Dr. Sviatoslav Braynov,
        Assistant Professor at UIS. The brochure of the conference can be found <a href="conferences/cddr2006/brochure06.pdf">her</a><a href="conferences/cddr2006/brochure06.pdf">e</a>.</p>
